# Practical Example

A financial institution deploys an AI-based fraud detection system that analyzes millions of payment transactions each day. During routine monitoring, the cybersecurity team identifies unusual prediction patterns and discovers that an attacker attempted to manipulate the training dataset used during a recent model update.

The organization immediately isolates the affected environment, validates the integrity of the training data, restores trusted datasets from secure backups, and retrains the AI model using verified information. Additional security controls, including stricter data validation procedures, enhanced access controls, and continuous monitoring, are implemented to prevent similar attacks.

By integrating AI security into its governance framework, the organization protects the integrity of its AI systems, maintains customer trust, and strengthens the resilience of its Artificial Intelligence Management System.

